reviews.text:
I placed an online order at this location, two sandwiches, and drove to pick them up.

Upon returning home, I discovered my sandwich was prepared incorrectly. It was missing vegetables, had vegetables I didn’t order, and the wrong sauce. I drove back to the store and asked that I be remade.

The worker opened the sandwich up and asked what was wrong with it. I explained what was wrong. She picked off a banana pepper and asked why I couldn’t just taken them off. I repeated that several things were wrong with and again asked for it to be made correctly.

She then proceeded to turn to the other customer and mock me I told the woman I didn’t appreciate being mocked to other customers.

I finally had enough and asked for my money back, to which she said “come back tomorrow, I can’t help you”.

I reached out to the franchisee (as his info is prominently posted in the Restaraunt). This was the response I got:

“I am very sorry for your inconvenience. I assure you the best service during your next visit. Thank you for being a loyal customer of Subway.”

How would he be able to assure anyone of receiving a correct sandwich, let along the “best service” when you approach a serious issue with a three sentence form email. Do not eat here.

After telling the lady I didn't want the brown cold cut meat on my sandwich she got really mad and refuse to serve me and then snatched my phone from me and then chased me out the store, I contacted corporate office they have yet to respond

Like the customer service, workers are nice but the place is quite small so it might be hard for some people to notice it from the outside on a street point of view. Neither less, sandwiches are great and food is always on stock here 👌 I would also  recommend this place for a quick bite to satisfy your hunger.

The food is good and the location is clean, but after the pandemic everything changed. They open at 9AM instead of 7AM and even then they are still not ready or not even open at 9AM like they said. It takes them a long time to help you, because they only have 1 person working. I usually have to wait until 10 am to go which is super inconvenient because I usually go to get breakfast before work.

Do not visit this subway. The staff is rude.  They also gave themselves a tip without asking. My meal was $17 and they took it upon themselves to round up to $20. The man that did it was the manager or owner. I did not authorize this.

I went here for my bff (overpriced) birthday outing. The atmosphere was okay, however the service staff could've been a lot better for the price point given the high price for their birthday party packages.
The package we purchased included 2 hours of unlimited bowling and unlimited alcoholic drinks (I ended purchasing about 1 hr).

To be honest,  the price wasn't really worth it. If you wanted unlimited drinks, you had to get 2 at a time because the "bartender" was slow as molasses (which was kind of AMFs fault being that they had one bartender on a Saturday night). Also, it didn't help that she was on the phone the whole time talking to her friends about her relationship problems instead of making drinks in a timely manner.

If I chose to visit another AMF, it definitely will not be this one....

Great spot to checkout. Solid 4-Star for me but I don't bowl much.
Has my favorite features: bowling, bar with good drinks and delicious food. I had the sampler and everything from the fries to wings were delicious. 😋 Drinks were great and strong. The actual bowling and equipment were good.
Now the wait was 30min on a busy night and with one person on the register renewing my game took a bit longer than I like.

Mr. Emerson, the manager is amazing. He was attentive to all of our needs and greeted us as if we were family. The entire staff was accommodating and they even brought food to our lanes. When it was time to leave, everyone asked if we had a good time and they genuinely seemed to care. Will be back.
Took my kids to have a night out on Sunday. They have a Sunday special after 6p. The margaritas were good and do try the tacos

Every employee was very helpful, the food was replenished as promised.  We celebrated a birthday, they honored my request and announced over intercom Happy Birthday to
the honoree. We did our part and finished our game, cake and clean up.  Just a very nice time, no problems. My only concern was no green veggies on the menu package.

My last visit, The cashier named "Papi" was VERY RUDE to me. I asked her for some fixings on the side and she responded "WHY!?" and followed with all attitude afterwards. I said never mind and drove down to New Carrollton's Subway and got greeted and served with no issues or questions what so ever. I had ordered several footlong subs and everyone doesn't like to same fixings. To make matters worst, a few weeks later my sister said she went to the same store and was treated TERRIBLE by the same cashier.  I wrote a letter to Subway's Corporates but they never responded back.  I've been going to Jersey Mike's ever since and so has my sister.
Excellent new subway. It has new decor and looks awesome. The staff was very courteous too!
Everything good except no cup for water!

Before placing an order, my daughter had to use the restroom which was out of order. I asked the 2 employees at the front and they disregard and ignored me when I asked if my child could use the employee restroom. Since they couldn't accommodate my child, I'll take my business elsewhere.
Ordered through UberEats, they forgot to put my ham on my forest ham sandwich. Luckily I had some shaved turkey at home and put it on my sandwich! So GHETTO!!!!

This is what they consider an order? I guess I was getting it for a child...$12.00 at it's finest. Never again and watch them make your order!!! Beef with broccoli and fire wok shrimp. So disappointed 😞

They're pretty good about making food and staying on top of making sure food is hot and available for serving throughout the business hours.

A bit iffy looking at their egg  rolls, they always look so dry and burnt that I wonder how long they've been out (but they're always hot the few times I've eaten them).

They definitely stick to the "recommended serving size" portions here. Don't expect an extra piece of chicken or 1 more green bean above their calorie count on the posted signs. I'm sure it helps them save costs in the long-term, but it has my belly empty on the short-term! Haha. The "bigger entree" is not worth the price. You just wind up spending too much money for a small side-entry.

To day  Sunday 07/31/22 I ordered panda Express for me and my wife. Pnn my plate I found a Hair  and it was really nasty. It made me  throw up. I really didn't  enjoy my food. It was a bad experience at this panda Express. If you go to this place always check your food and say something. I think that the workers need to use something on their head to stop dropping hair on people's food.  We work so hard to pay our food and at the end we don't enjoy it because you find out a hair on your plate.

No real options, limited menu.  The food was good though but having same old choices is tiring.  Parking is usually pretty good, and they do provide a good alternative to hamburgers.  The service is buffet line style, so you have to study what you are being served depending on who is there.

I’m giving this place a 1. My wife placed an order online so I could swing by and pick it up on the way home. When I arrive I tell them I’m there to pick up and gave them her first and last name, they immediately stated they needed to see the actual order receipt thru screen shot. My wife was not answering so I couldn’t get that, I told them I’m giving you her first and last name if the order is there with her name why are you making it difficult, they stated it’s their policy. I stated if I leave you will have to refund and possibly throw that food away the cashier stated “that’s ok” meaning we don’t care. So I left without the food. My wife drove back and told them it doesn’t say anywhere on the app customer must show receipt not only that her first and last name was on receipt. I think that was horrible customer service and I will never stop in that panda again.

Lenny's sell good food. But, they missed the mark on the last chicken and fries mumbo salt, pepper, ketchup. Mumbo was left off the chicken and only given on the side. The taste wasn't what I remembered. And minimal salt, pepper ketchup on fries. Never thought I would see the day that Danny's on 450 would be blowing you guys out the water nowadays.😒 😑
Fresh cooking oil, you can taste it with the wings. Try the steak-n-cheese egg roll. Thank me laters

Best chicken with fries and mumbo sauce you can find in the DMV area. The fries here aren't soggy and the chicken isn't so crispy its like biting into a brick. This is my go-to whenever I want carry-out. Lenny's has been around for ages and they take order right up until their closing time. Very friendly staff as well.

I've been a costumer from this restaurant and the service and food are excellent.
The fried rice is their specialty

Hasn't changed, moved away 15 years ago came back to visit family and first place for food I stopped was here I was like ohhhh they still here yes. Ordered me my wings fried rice with extra mumbo sauce and man delicious took me back 15 years so glad they haven't changed and the sauce I got extra to bring back home with me.

Observation - GM was in store making sure the staff was serving customers respectfully. Food was hot and GM thanked me for coming to Popeyes. I was grateful to see a manger keeping the staff on point. Spicy chicken was hot and not overly hooked.

Just came to eat for lunch. Ms. Angela took care of an upset customer and was super professional.

She even ordered her crew lunch for the day. That's what good leaders do!

I couldn't believe the quality of the meal I ordered! It was disappointing. I wanted a Chicken strip meal with a coupon! I got chicken breaded skin with hardly any real meat! I'm sorry to say this but why send Us a deal when it wasn't really worth the fund's I paid for it!
It's Popeyes! Not much to say here, but the chicken is cooked the way you like and the sauces are great. The drive through is weird, but the people are fast and friendly.
Took 9 months to go back and still  gave them some money for free. $24.25 and got half my order. I’m gonna make it forever this time!
The wings were okay. The fries were good for awhile with the bbq sauce.

Sign Says they close at 11pm. At 10:54 they already stopped serving. Wouldn't let me in to buy bottled drink. Very disappointing. If this store closes before 11pm on Fridays, I highly recommend the operating hours be updated on both the door sign and Google. I will take my dehydration elsewhere.
I can’t believe they even served me this. I go here all the time but this right here the fries are rubber and the chicken still looks alive….smh

First time here. Was interested in the whole wings. Excellent. Cooked perfectly, good Buffalo and garlic parmasan sauces. Cole slaw fresh. My husband got a large fry, very generous portion. Wait for take out wasn't too bad. A busy place is a good sign.  I'm not from the immediate area but would make the hour drive again.

This had been on the list for a while. The wing flavors looked really interesting so my wife and I got the 20pc and medium fries with four different flavors - Honey Lemon Pepper, Hot Lemon Pepper, Moon Dust, and Honey Old Bay. Our verdict was the same on all them - sooo salty. We could hardly taste the seasoning and the flavors on them. Ironically, they didn’t season the fries at all and they were really bland. The wings themselves were cooked really nice and crispy, but the salt made it hard to make it through our food and made us take breaks. Our meal total was $30. For the price and food quality, we won’t be visiting again.

plus_code.compound_code: W4GC+QH North Englewood, Greater Landover, MD, USA

reviews.text: My credit card processed at the pump but it wouldn’t pump unless I joined their text club. I went inside and they wanted to run my card again. I decided to try my luck elsewhere.

reviews.author_name: Archbishop Dr Smith Abrams Almasi MDiv DD THD PhD
reviews.text:
Excellent gas price always around this area.
The best discounts found around town. Try it. 7777 nice number too. Happy New Year 2022.

I was lost and late for an appointment. The cashier was nice but wasn’t sure of where the street was that I was looking for. He pulled out his phone and looked it up for me. Now why didn’t I think of that?  He was my savior that evening. Next time I’m in the area I’ll shop at this shell.

We got gas here, but my dog vomited in the car. I asked the staff member behind the bullet
Proof glass for some paper towels and he handed me one. I asked to use the restroom, which I was denied. The staff barely looked at me
They have gas if you need it, super small selection of snacks a drink, if you are from out of town I would not recommend stopping here.

I know its not the location fault but everything was extremely salty. The best thing I had was the funnel cake fries. Had the parm garlic loaded fries and it was just a sodium overload, I couldn't even finish it. Also had the mother cruncher? Whatever sauce on it was salty as well.

The fries were hot and ready. The chicken was a breaded pattie as I was expecting a real chicken breast. The service was fast but the tea tasted like soapy water was added instead of sugar. And there was no restroom so I was confused with the cleanliness of the overall establishment.

I really DO NOT like this Checkers location. This is the last time I will ever purchase food from them. First off, they always close way earlier than when they’re supposed to. Second, they rush every single thing you order. The only thing ever good is the fries. Tonight I ordered from them through door dash; my order was made in FIVE MINUTES. My chicken tenders were completely UNDERCOOKED literally pink and also some were rubbery. I ordered around 11pm and they stop taking door dash orders at 11:20pm. I know for a fact they rushed my food and that’s nasty and unsafe. Never again.

I ordered from Uber eats and in the receipt you can see I have 2 fries in the order but I am missing one and so I paid for something I didn’t receive I need free fries or something because this isn’t cool man.

I don't eat everything from checkers, but I have tried many menu items 😋 my favorite thing to eat when I'm out and about shopping and things is a vanilla and chocolate mixed shake and a large fry! The combination of sweet and salt is comforting to me 😁 it reminds me of my childhood Friday meals with my mom and dad, from McDonald's of fries and a vanilla shake 😋

Midnight pizza, pasta n wings snack! I was worried it would be cold after being advised 1 hour for delivery. But it was fresh, hot n delicious! Door Dash gets 0 for leaving my food at the door n didn’t even knock. But it wasn’t Pizza Hut fault! The food was great.

Now the one that look sloppy and foul && the cheese and pepperoni wasn’t all the way cooked. I usually don’t even go to this one I go to the one on up Annapolis rd which the pizza that looks GOOD is theirs. BUT THIS LOCATION never again and I mean NEVER. I wish I could give zero stars.

This was my first visit to this Pizza Hut location and I was pleased!  My carryout order was made well and met my expectations.  The food was hot, fresh, and tasted great.  The order was ready during the estimated timeframe.  The staff who gave me the food was pleasant, also.

I placed an order to try the big New Yorker. Well I didn't know that pizza hut started using doordash as a delivery service well doordash driver Michael A. did not follow my specific instructions to knock on my apartment door and wait for me to answer the door with my order instead he came into my apartment building and dropped it off in the lobby so he said. my building has over 100 apartments in it so who thinks somebody is going to come to the lobby and pick up food after you have left the building and left it unattended?anybody could have done anything or taken the food. I'm assuming somebody took the food because I did not go down there to look gor it. I recommend that you don't order from Pizza Hut on Annapolis Rd in Landover Hills MD or if your area restaurant is using doordash as delivery people. I have not gotten a refund I tried to call the specific Pizza Hut location on Annapolis Road in Landover Hills MD and could not reach a live person at the store I kept getting sent over to a customer service line where somebody was answering the phone out of Texas Pizza Hut you need to do better and get it together or be specific if you want your customer to come down to the car to pick up the orders that should be stated when the orders are placed online or on the phone if I had known that was what they were going to do I would have ordered from someplace else.

My order was for curbside pickup.   I parked right by the front door.  Called to let someone know I was there .  I gave the lady that answered the phone my name and said I was here for curbside pickup.   The lady told me to hold on.  After being on hold for 10 minutes I gave up and walked inside.  The person that waited on me inside said there was no vehicle listed for curbside pickup.   Well my whole problem is, I was on hold for 10 minutes,  why did not anyone come back to the phone and ask me what kind of vehicle I was driving.   I was put on hold and forgotten.   Imagine my shock and horror when I get home and discover that one of my 2 pizza's was wrong.   I didn't even bother to call back to the restaurant.   Thanks, for less than stellar customer service,  Eugene.

I come here often go Egusi soup served with pounded yam . I got turned on here by my friend and I have been coming ever since then.  If you are used to authentic African food you will know that De Ranch is the real deal. The people that matters in Africa community eat here

De Ranch is actually for the elite in African and Caribbean food  If  you ever think that the food is tasteless or not good enough for you, you must have the wrong taste bud. I will advise the fake reviewers to go to someone where else
This place is SO awesome! I mean the food was great as well as the customer service. Would give more stars if I could! Will definitely come back!!
Employees were friendly & pleasant. The Chicken jollof rice & greens were just ok. the chicken tasted like it was 4 or 5 days old though.

The Cassava Leaf Soup was 🔥 🔥🔥. The Chef poured a generous amount on top of my chicken and Jollof Rice. They definitely give you a good portion for your money.

De Ranch has 3 different areas. One is the dining room. The dining room gives you an antic afri-cuisine feel when you enter. The lounge gives you reggae vibes. The main area is where you order your food. The main area is also a bar with a heavy selection of alcoholic beverages.

If you want African, Caribbean or American food. De Ranch can service you!

This place is great! Atmosphere is chill and cool but the staff is also really friendly. They know what they’re doing and what they’re talking about, and you can tell making the customers happy is their main priority. Food is excellent. You can taste every spice each bite. I had Cassava with Chicken and Rice, Red Stew, Jerk Chicken and Egusi. I’m happy to find another spot closure to my ride home. Let me not forget they also have a nice Friday night happy hour with comedy show starting at 5pm with some delicious cocktails my favorite is the Punch 😀

No Bathroom. The store has all the snacks and drinks plus coffee and slurpies. They have tobacco products and the have lottery behind the glass. The gas was at a reasonable price and so was the things i got from inside. Good experience and clean environment for this gas station

Gas Station always has very suspect individuals just hanging out side of the store that always come up and ask you for money.  Most recently there was a man stabbed there and I have seen people lying on the ground high right beside pumps. No clue why the owners allow that around their station.  But I advise getting gas elsewhere.
Always has the most reasonably priced gas.  Large variety of items to choose from and can play the lottery.  Didn't like looking for a pencil to write down numbers

Very nice and pleasant and relaxing gas station at the auto department outstanding worked at the time and just and will help you to make sure that all things that you need for your vehicle to be fixed properly. Done
I bought $6.00 gas and my card was charged $20.00. That's so unfair and only reason I bought $6.00 gas I only buy gas at Costco and my tank was on empty.

If you are a seafood lover like I am and you're in the Landover Maryland area please stop by this 202 icon! NY Chicken and Fish have many platters where you and other person can dine for a little over $20.00.  The sides are fresh the rice is cooked to perfection 👌 and the fish taste as if it was just caught.
Fast friendly service.  I  always tip.  Just love the way the chicken and fish is battered,  so tastes.  Usable bathrooms a big plus.
Expensive for no reason. The fish meals comes with no drink and that's starting at $14. All the chicken meals comes with a can soda. On a positive note the fish is good.

I've been working in the area for about 3 months and this is the only place I come back to over and again. The chicken is great, fried fish is fantastic, burger the size of a whopper but reminds me flavor wise of a Krystal. Portions are huge and reasonably priced. Staff are always super friendly and helpful if an order is made wrong.
There's a small wait for food, but it's usually because they're making it fresh.
I recommend all day 👍
Food was great. The service and dinning area could be a little better but not terrible.  This is mainly a takeout spot.

I bought a single “cheesesteak” sub for $17 and it came with burger patties as the meat! Obviously this isn’t what’s in the picture and it’s not how they usually serve it. But they chose to sell this junk to me anyways. Super dry old patties that I simply couldn’t down as hungry as I was. Do NOT trust these people! Save your time and money and go elsewhere.

There food is terrible the customer service is terrible. I ordered a chicken cheesesteak and it hen I bit into it I immediately gagged. I know that wasn’t chicken that I just hit into. Would never go here again

I was a big fan of this place but their recent price increases appear to be price gouging. I am going to try Beijing Palace which also delivers and I hear is also really good.  Their price for an egg roll is $4 less than Landover Carryout. YES, $4 less per roll! An order of fried rice increased almost 7 dollars a container. I'm not sure what the owners are thinking.  I get that restaurant's need to adjust for increases in gas costs etc. but their price increase seems excessive.  As a 25-year customer who would willingly support an increase I can't support price gouging.
The food is always flavorful and the order is always correct. I recommend if your craving carry out!
Landover This restaurant is famous for Chinese food at excellent prices, so whoever wants to book a table for him and enjoy with his friends
We got a large meat lovers with veggies added, hand-tossed crust, and a salad...prettiest salad loaded with freshness. This is the best pizza I've ever eaten, hands down!
The sauce is somewhat sweet, the cheese is well done and the crust is nice and fluffy. The interior of the shop is a little dingy, but the prices are solid, and they are consistent.

I Ordered From This Pizza Bolis Couple Tymes & They Been Iight, No Problems, Except For The Fact That They Never Give Me Seasonings & Peppers When I Ask But This Time. Im Done. Im 0.5 Miles Away & It Took Them An Hour & A Half To Deliver, No Seasonings Or Sauces On Side Like I Requested & The Pizza Was Terrible, No Extra Cheese When I Paid More Money For It. Never Gotten A Pizza From That Looks Like This. My Friends & I Ate One Piece And Hated It. I Called Back But They Played Closed. I Will Be Returning This Terrible Pizza
Really enjoyed the stromboli. Fast delivery on a Tuesday night, about 30  minutes. Reasonable prices.

Cheese pizza with mushroom and chicken was fresh and delicious. The garlic sauce on the side was a great touch. It was ready sooner than I was expecting. Very happy with my first order. Good job guys!

plus_code.compound_code: W4G7+FP Landover, Greater Landover, MD, USA

reviews.text: Combo fried rice and spring rolls are good. Asked for extra spicy, and they made it just right. Rice was little greasy than other carry out but it was flavorful. Rolls were crunchy. Kung pow chicken was full of veggies & peanuts, w 5 small slivers of thinly sliced chicken. Friendly service & clean lobby area.

I was greeted as I walked up to order my food. I receive my food. I was thank and she said have a good night. Service is always great and the food is great too.  I always feel welcome and very well taken care of,when I place my order here. I Highly  recommend this spot
I love the family that runs this establishment!!! It's not the best looking place but the quality is consistent and I never fell like I've wasted my money ordering late night or lunch.

I'm telling yall do not order from here let me start of by saying the total was 20$plus a tip.... so I got a teriyaki chicken white rice and I'm heated right now, literally my food smells like iron  the sause smells like it was watered down and the chicken taste rubbery I called back and told her my chicken wasn't fully cooked instead of apologizing about giving me non cooked chicken, she just said that's how we make it here, if that's the standard and considered ok it's a big red flag and a no no! China fong restaurant on Annapolis road is 10x better .
The seafood soup is really good. Loaded with seafood adm vegetables!

In case if you wanna order Chow Mein, here how it looks like(not a single piece of a noodle, just a juicy white vegetables). It supposed to be a dish with the noodle right?! Mein is a noodle in Chinese for god’s sake LOL and I know that. I went back to ask them if it’s a correct order they were confused in the beginning and then explained Lo mein is a noodle chow mein is just a vegetable just to get rid of me LOL. I’ve been ordering Chinese food for a decade never have I ever seen Chow mein like this tho. Oh and also they gave me that fried noodle like a compensate. Thanks. Won’t return! And be careful folks.
Food was fine, order was not correct, wings little bland. Person taking order needs to listen more carefully. Will try there again.

I keep giving this place nance after chance to get it right because when I first moved around here about 2 years ago, I was satisfied with the orders I've made. I don't know if someone else has taken over or if the originally cooks were replaced but the food is starting to get nastier and nastier and the portions smaller. I have several issues with this place.

1. The Drivers.

I understand that we live in a not so good area. The drivers are scared of being robbed so they will not deliver the food to your door. Instead, they will make you come to the car and get it. And if you're not out the door about 15 seconds after they call you, the will obnoxiously blow the horn until you come outside not knowing if there is a disability that you suffer from that prohibits you from doing so. Once you get to the car, they will yell "Give me the money". First of all, don't tell me to give you anything. How about we great each other with hellos instead ? Today, the driver actually snatched the money out of my hand and then said something which I'm pretty sure was either a racial slur or something smart in his own language. I asked him to repeat it and he threw my items at me. I immediately called the store and asked to speak with a manager who seemed like he could careless about my complaint against his driver.

2. The Portions.

The lunch portions are starting to get smaller and smaller. They're giving you more vegetables than meat in everything. A shrimp egg roll is no longer a shrimp egg roll but a egg roll with spring roll filling a baby one baby shrimp. I ordered a steak and cheese and the the bread was hot but the meat was damn near cold.

3. The Lack-of-Respect.

You have a business in OUR neighborhood. Don't you think that you should show us some type of respect considering the fact that it is us who are ordering from you that pays your bills to keep your business open.

I will NEVER order from here again and I hope that anyone who goggle this address for delivery reads this review and doesn't order from there either.

They tried to smart-alecks with my order. I ordered the vegetable sandwich with lettuce, they sent bread with lettuce in it, nothing else. Then they tried to blame me, because their online order stated a lettuce sandwich, it doesnt, it clearly indicates the order was a vegetable sub with lettuce added to it. Incompetent and extremely rude people, don't order from here.

I have been eating here for years and my food has always been fresh, just flat out good. I even will by pass other carryouts just to get to them. Today I ordered shrimp fired rice, shrimp/broccoli, general tso shrimp, & egg rolls. I found 3 little black bugs in the food and the first one I said maybe it was the season then I started to just look throughout the food and 2 more was in the shrimp/broccoli. I called back to let them know look I found bugs in the food and the young female that takes the orders tell me that wasn't possible. I told her that I was on the way back to bring them the food she just keep telling me that it's not possible. I get there with the food and the bugs she still saying it not possible with the bug in her face as if I put the bugs in the food. Then she states the I should left the bugs in the food because I had put them on a napkin.

plus_code.compound_code: W4J2+P4 Landover, Greater Landover, MD, USA

reviews.text: DO NOT GO HERE !!  I Gave This Place A 1 Start Because That Was The Only Option.  If I could I Would Give Them A -100 . First They Are Rude As Fk . Second The Food Is Comparable To Dog Shh . I Wouldn't Even Feed My Dog Anything From This Place . I've Been Eating Jamaican Food All My Life And Have NEVER Seen Food Like This . I Paid $60 And Had To Throw The Food away . It Smelled Soooooo Bad . The Coco Bread Smelled Sour . They Should Be Ashamed To call Their Place A restaurant. More Like A Dog Food Establishment.

ABSOLUTELY DO NOT, I REPEAT, DO NOT EVER EAT HERE. THE FOOD IS OLD/OVERCOOKED/BURNED/SUBQUALITY. I WOULD NOT FEED IT TO A DYING DOG. YOU SHOULD BE ASHAMED OF CALLING YOURSELF A GRILL. STAY IN YOUR LANE. STICK TO DRY/CANNED GOODS ONLY.

We just ate from here about two hours ago and we must say that the food was great. Everything was hot and fresh. The employees was very nice and helpful. They gave us so much food its going to take two days to eat. We will definitely come again soon.

I ordered jerk chicken I watched the cashier touch my chicken with his bare hands no gloves to pack up for me. I immediately called him out. Luckily the manager walked in and heard my rant and gave me a refund. Dont eat here very unsanitary.
There was hair in my food hiding in the ox tails and the plantain was under cops and the rice was over cooked great customer service but taste is not there yet.

I have been to several Ledo's Pizza locations and I have NEVER been disappointed. Absolutely delicious. This location was clean, the staff was friendly, the location was convenient to the beltway and my order came out in a timely manner. I will definitely revisit and try other things on the menu. Ps, we got a 1/2 & 1/2 pizza: half veggie lovers & half deluxe, 18" w/30 slices, total $33.33. Enough for leftovers. No cooking. I am a happy camper 🙂

Since moving to NYC from the Maryland/DC area I truly miss Ledo's!  There isn’t anything like it and they need to bring one to NYC and shut it down up here...please! :).  But for now, I always make it a point to get a pizza whenever I come back down to visit...you should too

I love Ledo's pizza since Shakey's is gone but moving forward I'm not sure who prepared that pizza let me add it was the football playoffs advertising horrible. In my opinion just go and order your special pizza and hope for the best the days to go???? Keep hope alive... ME TOO....

Female employee with red ponytail and long lashes need to be fired her attitude is horrible and has no customer service  she is very rude and unprofessional.  She is casher on at 10pm 2/24/23. I won't be coming back here again I came from north Carolina and a friend told me it was good but I was so insulted by this uncircumcised horrible human .the owner needs to fire this young woman she is bring business down!!!!!!!

Staff is rude and unprofessional. At the register “helping” customers while on their phone giving no eye contact and not acknowledging anyone. I’ve been in customer service for almost 2 decades and I don’t understand what kind of training they are giving their staff
